<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1155,1973]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1300,1324]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gyulai, 2019" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,529,1301,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[322,529,1301,1325]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Valeria wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[536,596,1301,1325]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[536,596,1301,1325]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[611,673,1301,1325]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1692,1714]" captionTargetBox="[159,1416,179,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,167,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Adults. 1. Valeria wassalberti sp. n., holotype, Iran, prov. Hormozgan, 80 km N. of Bandar Abbas, slide GYP 5057 (coll. P. Gyulai); 2. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Kermanshah, Zagros, slide GYP 5059 (coll. P. Gyulai)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3534838" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3534838/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) is a medium sized species, similar only to the 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wiltshire, 1957)" authorityName="Wiltshire" authorityYear="1957" baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis box="[1182,1366,1301,1325]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Valeria carducha</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wiltshire, E. P." pageId="0" pageNumber="394" refId="ref1413" refString="Wiltshire, E. P. (1957) The Lepidoptera of Iraq. Dorking, Alard and Son, London, 162 pp." type="book" year="1957">Wiltshire, 1957</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[294,361,1337,1361]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1692,1714]" captionTargetBox="[159,1416,179,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,167,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Adults. 1. Valeria wassalberti sp. n., holotype, Iran, prov. Hormozgan, 80 km N. of Bandar Abbas, slide GYP 5057 (coll. P. Gyulai); 2. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Kermanshah, Zagros, slide GYP 5059 (coll. P. Gyulai)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3534838" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3534838/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
; the 
<typeStatus box="[413,506,1337,1361]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">holotype</typeStatus>
(male) and 
<typeStatus box="[636,738,1337,1361]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">paratypes</typeStatus>
are figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, G. &amp; Ronkay, L. &amp; Gyulai, P." box="[904,1279,1337,1361]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" refId="ref1298" refString="Ronkay, G., Ronkay, L. &amp; Gyulai, P. (2011) Cuculliinae II and Psaphidinae-The Witt Ctalogue. Vol. 5. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 380 pp." type="book" year="2011">Ronkay, Ronkay &amp; Gyulai (2011))</bibRefCitation>
, from which it is distinguished by the size and some of the external and genitalia features. The distinctive external key features are as follows: the new species is significantly smaller than 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[732,859,1409,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis box="[732,859,1409,1433]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[875,955,1409,1433]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" unit="mm" value="27.0">27 mm</quantity>
, versus 
<quantity box="[1043,1161,1409,1433]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" unit="mm" value="35.0" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="32.0">32–38 mm</quantity>
, no significant difference between the males and females of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[525,652,1445,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis box="[525,652,1445,1469]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the ground colour of vesture of head and thorax and forewings is light greyish, versus light brownish and somewhat darker, with much stronger, darker medial fascia and postmedial line in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Hindwings of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gyulai, 2019" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[420,570,1517,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[420,570,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[578,639,1517,1541]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[578,639,1517,1541]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are also greyish, unicolorous, while more variegated, whitish with brown suffusion in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[323,449,1553,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis box="[323,449,1553,1577]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly on the main veins and in the margin. Cilia lighter, whitish, the discal spot in the hindwings is more conspicuous in the new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1155,1973]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
In the female genitalia, the differences between 
<taxonomicName authority="Gyulai, 2019" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[706,854,1625,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[706,854,1625,1649]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[860,919,1625,1649]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[860,919,1625,1649]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[933,995,1625,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1764,1786]" captionTargetBox="[159,1416,179,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,167,1672]" captionText="FIGURES 3–5. Female genitalia. 3. Valeria wassalberti sp. n., holotype, Iran, prov. Hormozgan, 80 km N. of Bandar Abbas, slide GYP 5057 (coll. P. Gyulai); 4. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Kermanshah, Zagros, slide GYP 5059 (coll. P. Gyulai); 5. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Khorassan, Kopeth Dagh, slide GYP 5058 (coll. P. Gyulai)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613672/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[1055,1184,1625,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis box="[1055,1184,1625,1649]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1197,1291,1624,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–5" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1764,1786]" captionTargetBox="[159,1416,179,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,167,1672]" captionText="FIGURES 3–5. Female genitalia. 3. Valeria wassalberti sp. n., holotype, Iran, prov. Hormozgan, 80 km N. of Bandar Abbas, slide GYP 5057 (coll. P. Gyulai); 4. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Kermanshah, Zagros, slide GYP 5059 (coll. P. Gyulai); 5. Valeria carducha (Wiltshire, 1957), Iran, prov. Khorassan, Kopeth Dagh, slide GYP 5058 (coll. P. Gyulai)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613672/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
; one from SE 
<collectingCountry box="[151,194,1661,1684]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
and one from NE 
<collectingCountry box="[392,439,1661,1685]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
), are found in the shape, size and sclerotization of the antrum–ostium complex, ductus bursae and appendix bursae. The new species has calycular, less sclerotized antrum–ostium complex with V–shaped medial incision of the dorsal plate of ostium, while those are more sclerotized, broader with more or less broadly U–shaped ostium plate in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[238,338,1769,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis box="[238,338,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[380,529,1769,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti">
<emphasis box="[380,529,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ductus bursae is much narrower (particularly its posterior part tube–like and not sclerotized); whereas it is much broader, anterior section is more sclerotized, wrinkled, posterior section evenly dilated but shorter in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[338,438,1841,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis box="[338,438,1841,1865]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in the new species, the appendix bursae is larger and more prominent. The correct separation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gyulai, 2019" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2019" box="[181,330,1877,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wassalberti" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[181,330,1877,1901]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">V. wassalberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[338,399,1877,1901]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[338,392,1877,1901]" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[451,636,1877,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis box="[451,636,1877,1901]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Valeria carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is supported by the allopatric distribution of the two species; the new species is known only from the southernmost 
<collectingCountry box="[601,647,1913,1936]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
, not very far from the Persian Gulf, whereas the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiltshire" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[1160,1343,1913,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Valeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carducha">
<emphasis box="[1160,1343,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Valeria carducha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not so local, occurs both in 
<collectingCountry box="[374,417,1949,1972]" name="Iraq" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iraq</collectingCountry>
(eastern parts) and 
<collectingCountry box="[627,670,1949,1972]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
(from the NW and SW to the NE of 
<collectingCountry box="[1063,1110,1949,1973]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="394">Iran</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3534838" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3534838" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3534838/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" startId="1.[151,258,1692,1714]" targetBox="[159,1416,179,1660]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1692,1858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">
